comment: I love the asmr moment of watching Kiu and his team get focused on a task/styling hair, I sometimes wish it could last longer ï¸ Kiu's videos are always great to learn something new, laugh a lot, and got a bit of asmr in the process!
First of all, she's adorable. Secondly, I love the conversation you guys had.

It must have been so fun for them to work with Scandinavian fine hair, we have a special kind of hair and when I was in Japan they were like omg omg omg haha, it just has a very special feeling to it, very different from Asian hair. It is amazing she has been able to keep that lenght and also keep it healthy because Scandinavian hair very easily break off from smallest things, she really is the Norwegian Rapunsel, sending love from Swedish neighbor!

I hope that she will do whatever she wants with her hair! I am mixed and I had frizzy hair before shaving it all. My mom hated the idea until she saw me really happy when I came back from the salon. I wanted to do that since I was 9 years old, now I'll soon be 18 and it was the best decision I made. Don't let others decide for you!!! If you don't like it, it will grow again, it's just hair, don't worry
I had hair down to mid-calf when I was in high school and college, but never again. I got tired of taking care of it. Watching Kiu and his staff work with clients is always facinaiting.

Fighting to all with ridiculously long hair! The struggle is real!

I love her hair . I can so relate, I have long hair like her and live in China people here are always asking me if it is hard to care for.  But I have very fine hair so I barely notice it.  I have had it bra strap length waist length hip length now bottom of my butt and don't really notice a difference except I feel more beautiful with it long and healthy my husband loves it.  Washing it and combing it takes like 10-15 minutes I use a good conditioning balm and only wash it 2-3 times a week then I just blow dry it for a few minutes and just clip it up and let it air dry it takes me under a min. to put it in a braid or bun.  my bun can be small no matter the length my hair is fine I used a bun volumizer donut thing til it reached my butt haha. So hair texture makes a huge difference I have found plus I don't want heat damage so I only straighten it or curl it for special events once in a while and I go to the salon for that.  They do this gorgeous braided headband on me in China and curl the ends it is my favorite fancy hairstyle .  I actually find shorter hairstyles much more difficult because with fine hair it takes a lot to style them and it is hard to just clip them up.  In fourth grade I tried an inverted bob I begged my mom for and omg if my parents didnt blow dry it for me every morning I wouldnt leave the house my fine hair would stick out like crazy.  My mom and dad were so glad when that grew out

She's super cute and I love how adventurous she is! However, I can tell that her hair is really damaged starting from the halfway point down the rest of the length and she needs to get it cut. If she changes her mind and wants to keep growing it, she's going to need to get those dead ends chopped off first and start applying a leave-in conditioner, hair oil, or both on the ends after she finishes washing and to try to break the habit of sleeping on a towel with wet hair since the hair is more fragile when wet and combining it with the friction from the towel can cause hair breakage over time. Using a heat protectant spray would also be a good idea for her (or anyone) if she regularly heat-styles her hair.
